"title": "7621: disciples, calling of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7621",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The term is applied to Christians in general, not to the Twelve only. It emphasises the importance of Jesus Christ's followers learning from Christ as their teacher.</p>\n<h2>Disciples learning from their master</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:16\">ISA 8:16</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos7:14\">AMO 7:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:35\">1KI 20:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:8\">NEH 3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:11\">ISA 19:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:24\">MAT 10:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:18\">MRK 2:18</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:33\">LUK 5:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:40\">LUK 6:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:35\">JHN 1:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:28\">JHN 9:28</a></p>\n<h2>Those referred to as disciples in the NT</h2>\n<h3>The disciples as the apostles</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:1-Matt10:2\">MAT 10:1–10:2</a></strong> <em>The apostles were uniquely appointed as founding pillars of the church, but in some respects they were also representative disciples.</em></p>\n<h3>The disciples as believers in general</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19\">MAT 28:19</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:1-Acts19:2\">ACT 19:1–19:2</a></strong> <em>Christian believers, not fully mature.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:13\">LUK 6:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:17\">LUK 6:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:2\">ACT 6:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:26\">ACT 11:26</a></p>\n<h3>The disciples as an intimate circle of believers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:1\">MAT 18:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:10\">MRK 4:10</a></p>\n<h2>How disciples are called</h2>\n<h3>It sometimes implies physically following Jesus Christ and leaving everything</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:19\">MAT 4:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:16-Mark1:20\">MRK 1:16–1:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:18-Matt8:22\">MAT 8:18–8:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:57-Luke9:60\">LUK 9:57–9:60</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:9\">MAT 9:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:14\">MRK 2:14</a></p>\n<h3>Calling in a more general spiritual sense</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:19\">JHN 21:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:23\">LUK 9:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:25-Luke14:27\">LUK 14:25–14:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:12\">JHN 8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:26\">JHN 12:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:22\">JHN 21:22</a></p>\n<h2>How disciples learn from Jesus Christ the teacher</h2>\n<h3>By repeating the words of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:1-Luke11:4\">LUK 11:1–11:4</a></strong> <em>The rhythmical form of much of Jesus Christ's teaching suggests he intended his words to be remembered verbatim.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:3-Matt5:10\">MAT 5:3–5:10</a></p>\n<h3>By signs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:11\">JHN 2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:37\">MRK 5:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:40\">MRK 5:40</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:51\">LUK 8:51</a></p>\n<h3>By understanding the OT Scriptures</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:45\">JHN 1:45</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:31-Luke18:33\">LUK 18:31–18:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:27\">LUK 24:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:32\">LUK 24:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:44-Luke24:45\">LUK 24:44–24:45</a></p>\n<h3>By understanding the parables</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:11-Mark4:12\">MRK 4:11–4:12</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:10-Matt13:11\">MAT 13:10–13:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:9-Luke8:10\">LUK 8:9–8:10</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:34\">MRK 4:34</a></p>\n<h3>By practical experience of mission</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:23-Luke10:24\">LUK 10:23–10:24</a></strong> <em>These words follow the sending out of the seventy-two.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:6-Mark6:11\">MRK 6:6–6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:1-Luke9:2\">LUK 9:1–9:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:1\">MAT 10:1</a></p>\n<h3>In periods of being alone with Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:31\">MRK 6:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:21\">MAT 16:21</a></p>\n<h3>In spite of their faulty understanding</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:25\">LUK 24:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:32\">MRK 9:32</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:45\">LUK 9:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:34\">LUK 18:34</a></p>",
